    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's the complete implementation plan for `next/geo`:\n\n---\n\n### What gets created (4 new files + 1 edit)\n\n**1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation (mirrors `user-agent.ts`):\n- `export interface Geo` — 7 optional string fields: `city`, `country`, `countryCode`, `region`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `timezone`\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` constant — 10-entry lookup map (US→\"United States\", GB→\"United Kingdom\", etc.)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers)` — reads `x-vercel-ip-*` headers, falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for countryCode, derives `country` via lookup\n- `geo(req)` — thin wrapper calling `geoFromHeaders(req.headers)`\n- `isInRegion(geo, regions)` — case-insensitive `countryCode` membership check\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula returning km\n\n**2. `packages/next/geo.js`** — Exact `server.js` pattern: `geoExports` object + `module.exports` + individual `exports.xxx` for named ESM import support\n\n**3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — Exact `server.d.ts` pattern: `export type { Geo }` + `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` from `next/dist/...`\n\n**4. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Jest tests (co-located, `describe`/`it`/`expect`): 10 cases covering Vercel headers, Cloudflare fallback, missing headers, `isInRegion` (match/no-match/case-insensitive/missing code), NY→London distance ~5570 ±100 km, country name lookup, unknown country code\n\n**5. `packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (line 43), before `\"router.js\"` (alphabetical: f < g < r)",
